I move amendment No. 2:In page 7, between lines 32 and 33, to insert the following:"(4) The Minister shall consider the adequacy or otherwise of a civil defence plan and/or a revised civil defence plan so as to ensure, as far as is practicable, that such plan meets with the criteria as set out in subsection (3) and in considering same, the Minister will consult with any or all of the following:(a) the Minister for the Environment, Community and Local Government;
(b) the Radiological Protection Institute of Ireland;
(c) Environmental Protection Agency;
(d) Civil Defence Officers Association;
(e) an Garda Síochána.".
